RACE.RACE_TEXT: THISTLEDOWN RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 90. Allowance Purse 28000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OPTIONAL OR OHIO BRED. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 13 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 13 Allowed 4 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RHYTHMIC RULER sped to the lead soon after the start, set the pace off the rail, drifted out to the five path entering the stretch, was put to right handed urging near the furlong marker, the rider switched to a left handed crop in near the sixteenth pole striking his mount once, drifted out to the eight path through the final stages and won under a hand ride. MR LOOOCH bore in at the start bumping RAISE THE PURSE causing a chain reaction of bumping to his inside, stalked the pace three wide into the turn, drew closer outside the winner, was carried out to the six path at the top of the stretch then to mid track through the final sixteenth of a mile and finished well clear for second while being checked. SUSIE'S KID altered course sharply to the outside at the start and passed tiring rivals outside. RAISE THE PURSES was bumped between horses at the start and failed to menace. O CIGANO also bumped between rivals at the start, pressed the pace two wide and was through after a half. GARRETT was brushed at the start and had brief speed. THE STEWARDS POSTED THE INQUIRY SIGN AND THE RIDER OF MR LOOOCH LODGED A CLAIM OF FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF THE WINNER FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE IN THE STRETCH, ALSO, THE RIDER OF RAISE THE PURSES LODGED A CLAIM OF FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF MR LOOOCH FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE AT THE START. AFTER REVIEW THE STEWARDS DISALLOWED BOTH CLAIMS OF FOUL AND UPHELD THE ORIGINAL ORDER OF FINISH.
